LEX The Held Apart.

"First Person" is a person.
"Gap" is a person.
"Swordsman" is a person.
"Canonical Bytes" is a text.
"Seed" is a text.
"Witness Draw" is a text.

The First Person appoints the Gap, and appoints the Swordsman.

CLAUSE: Derive.
The Gap may register the Canonical Bytes, and afterwards certify the Seed, and afterwards send the Witness Draw to the Swordsman.
